Problem: ch2_prob10

Given:
- Force \( F = 65 \, \text{kN} \)

---

**[FBD: First Diagram]**
- A force \( F \) acting at an angle of \( 65^\circ \) from the horizontal axis, with components \( F_x \) and \( F_y \) resolved along the x and y axes.
- Angles shown: \( 40^\circ \) and \( 50^\circ \) from the vertical and horizontal respectively, with \( 15^\circ \) also indicated.

Equations:
\[
\begin{cases}
F_x = -F \cos 65^\circ = -65 \cos 65^\circ \\
\underline{F_x = -27.5 \, \text{kN}}
\end{cases}
\]

\[
\begin{cases}
F_y = -F \sin 65^\circ = -65 \sin 65^\circ \\
\underline{F_y = -58.9 \, \text{kN}}
\end{cases}
\]

---

**[FBD: Second Diagram]**
- The same force \( F \) resolved into normal \( F_n \) and tangential \( F_t \) components along axes rotated by \( 40^\circ \).

Equations:
\[
\begin{cases}
F_n = -F \sin 40^\circ = -65 \sin 40^\circ \\
\underline{F_n = -41.8 \, \text{kN}}
\end{cases}
\]

\[
\begin{cases}
F_t = -F \cos 40^\circ = -65 \cos 40^\circ \\
\underline{F_t = -49.8 \, \text{kN}}
\end{cases}
\]
